value.0: "I cannot discuss this further with you. Keep searching for the truth and I am sure you will find it. Anything else?"

This beautiful young woman is surrounded by an aura of power and mystique. You recognize her as the spellcaster on the ramparts who brought your dispute with the Masked Man to its premature conclusion. She arches an eyebrow as you approach.
"So, the hero I thought I had killed has finally come to Yenna for a visit. You aren't very much to look at, sadly, but there is something unusual about you."
"So, the hero I thought I had killed has finally come to Yenna for a visit. You have a rather ordinary countenance, but something about you draws the eye."
"So, the hero I thought I had killed has finally come to Yenna for a visit. I must say you are a ravishing young thing!"
"I find you rather fascinating. What is your purpose here? I imagine you come about the election, or maybe for some magic items? Better yet, maybe you have come just for the conversation..."
"Leaving so soon? I do hope you will come and visit me again. You are... an interesting individual."
"Of course. I have a few interesting things you might find useful."
"Why don't we take a little time and get to know each other better. I have a few questions for you."
"I took some time to do some research about you. It seems to me that you enjoy traveling with what could generously be called a group of misfits."
"There is a common link that binds you, a thread of great suffering you have each faced. But you are the mystery, <FirstName>. In a group of misfits, it would seem you are the misfit."
"I have no cause to insult you. And I don't want you to make the mistake of thinking I find you 'normal' either."
"I don't think you're normal, far from it. I delved into the mystery of who you are, and I have divined something very interesting. Would you like to know what I found?"
"Then I suppose you shall remain ignorant of the truth. I personally have no time for ignorance. It shall be interesting watching you though."
"What would you like from me?"
"I used my spells to divine some of it... called on otherworldly sources to ask questions, that sort of thing. It really did lead to some interesting answers. Want to know?"
"Before I tell you, I would like to ask you a question. What is your earliest childhood memory?"
"You must have a strong mind, to have captured that image. That must have been very traumatic for you."
"Yes, sometimes the mind blocks out those horrible tragedies. It must have been very traumatic watching your parents die right before your eyes."
"Yes, that must have been a difficult time for you, after your parents were killed. Strange that you don't remember them dying right before your eyes."
"That must have been before they were killed then. A very early memory. Or were they your adoptive parents?"
"I am afraid they did die, while you were very young. You witnessed the event, but must have blocked it out. I am sorry if that comes as a surprise to you."
"Your parents died while you were very young. You witnessed the event, but must have blocked it out. I am sorry if that comes as a surprise to you."
"My source believed you would remember such a tragic moment, and though I am bound not to reveal who it is, I have good reason to believe she knows what she is talking about."
"I am magically bound in such a way that I cannot reveal who she is, or what... why... hmm, apparently I cannot even say that. It doesn't matter. If you pay attention, you will figure it out."
"Someone as... remarkable as her... leaves little traces of their... activities, as they move around. That is how I discovered... I guess that's as much as I can say about that."
"I would recommend you speak to Garrot at the Silver Lily. Tell him I sent you... I'm sure he will be more... helpful than I can be."
"There is one thing I can tell you though, because it is based on something my own magic revealed."
"My pleasure. There is one thing I can tell you though, because it is based on something my own magic revealed."
"This conversation was about misfits; well, you are also a misfit. You have blood of some other race. I cannot be specific, but I know that you have some kind of outsider blood in your ancestry."

value.0: "You appear to be of <race> blood, but appearances are often deceiving. Now, that is all I can tell you about this subject. What else should we discuss?"
Yenna winks. "Why, did I let that little detail slip? How very careless of me."
"I have special protective spells cast on my tower that let me know if someone lies to me. She lied to me several times, but not about this."
"I do not know why she is telling you this, but it is the truth, <FirstName>, at least she believes it is the truth."
"I would say that all depends on your point of view, doesn't it? I feel that it is always good to gain knowledge."
"I am saddened that you have chosen not to continue your travels with the others, but I suppose you had your reasons. I fear you will miss out on a great deal without them."
"That is generous. I would have called us something far worse than misfits."
"One could say that since we are all misfits, we fit perfectly."
"An elegant answer from a noble being, Jaboli. I would also agree with you fully."
"Who you calling a misfit, lady? Why I... <StartAction>[hack, choke]</Start> erp... sorry, choked on a chicken foot there... all better now. What was I saying?"
"Gentle, good Trip, I mean no harm with my words. I think yours is a very interesting group."
"You think we're the misfits? Har, you've never seen the <lad/lass> in action then. You wanna talk about misfits?"
"Ah, fiery Calibast, I sense a tragic tale in your soul, but what else could drive a noble Azer from his home?"
"And what questions do you have?"
"What would you like to discuss?"
"I spend most of my time here in my tower, so I am not the best person to ask for such information. Someone like Dynschall the priest spends more time with the people, you should ask him."
"I am the only member of the guild and my time is spent helping the people with minor problems, doing research to benefit the keep, and occasionally trying to get some rest."
"Despite being the smallest guild in the keep, the scarcity of mages in our world gives me a great deal of prestige and power. Do you have other questions?"
"Magic was once very common, thousands of years ago, but for some unknown reason fewer people in each generation have been born with the ability to wield arcane powers."
"Many of those who are born with the ability are not even powerful enough to be anything more than apprentices. It is a problem I have pondered many times, but I can find no good answer."
"What other questions do you have?"

value.0: "You are a practitioner of the arcane arts, so I suppose this is more than just a question out of curiosity. The truth is, you can join, but there are only a few things I can offer you."

"The first is a discount off the merchandise I offer. There is also a small stipend for defense of the keep, which I would willingly give you part of. I would also vote for you in the election... seems fair."
"But to join, I would like you to do something for me first."
"Because that is the way the world works. If you want something from someone you have to do something for them."
"My familiar, Zebulun, a pseudodragon, has a habit of disappearing for short periods of time. He enjoys finding strange hiding spots that people cannot get into."
"When I need him, I can reach out with my mind and contact him, usually. I know that the rascal is still within the keep, I would have known if he had left, but I cannot seem to find him."
"I fear that something has befallen the poor dear. I propose to change you into a faerie dragon, so that you may find whereever he might be hidden."
"I guess you must be busy. Just keep your eyes open and if you find him, tell him to come back."
"I appreciate the effort. I would be most pleased to have another member in the guild."
"I shall shift your shape right now. Good luck in your hunt."
"I could, but I have certain spells in effect that I need to keep my eye on. There have been some strange magical emminations from the caves east of the keep."
"I am trying to determine exactly where they are coming from, and what they are doing. If my spells are effective, I will be able to tell the next lord or lady exactly where our enemy is hiding."

value.0: "Of course, what else would you care to discuss?"

"Sir Becket's greed is limited only by his simple mind. He is devious, but not bright. Charming, yet not charismatic. There is actually very little to recommend him as the ruler of anything, including his own life."
"Enivid makes a good Hand, but she doesn't have enough experience outside the keep. It limits her view and makes her vulnerable to stereotypical thinking."
"I will tell you right up front, I don't care for Enivid or Sir Becket as far as making them my ruler. Enivid makes a good Hand, but she doesn't have enough experience outside the keep."
"Let me get to know you a bit better, and chances are I will vote for you... if I think you are trustworthy. Are you willing to share some of your background?"
A defiant glint passes across her eyes and is gone, quickly replaced with a dull blankness that tells you nothing. She waits for you to continue.

"I cast my spells from the ramparts, starting with those that would affect large numbers of the enemy. Flames, blades, ice, lightning... all of these things were my weapons against the Masked Man's forces."

"When I saw both you and he converging on the gates, I knew nothing good could come of such a conflict. I had a firegem in my possession and worked to cast it before the two of you could come to blows."
The glint in her eyes comes back, vicious now. "Trust me, I tried! And the masked man, too... I did what I could but now my hands are tied."
"Hate me for it if you wish but you may still need me in the end."
"He is in the prophecies, as are you. More than that I cannot say."
"Does the day favor you, Lord of the Keep? Allow me to be of some assistance..."
"I spoke to Garrot."
"Goodbye."
"Let me see what you have for sale."
